



Sir
Cambridge Sept. 10. 1775



Capt. Bayler waits upon you to receive the Specie prepared for Col. Arnold. You will at the same Time be pleased to pay him so much Continental Money as will make up the whole Sum 1000 lawful: A regular Warrt will be sent you in a Day or two which there are some Inconveniences in drawing at present.1 I am Sir Your most Obed. Hble
